Trader Sues ICE Over Stolen Emissions Permits, Point Carbon Says

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-06-06T16:58:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/trader-sues-ice-over-stolen-emissions-permits-point-carbon-says.html
An unidentified trader is taking
legal action against  London ’s ICE Futures Europe after buying
stolen European Union carbon permits on the exchange,  Point
Carbon  reported without saying where it got the information.  The trade prompting the lawsuit, which seeks compensation,
took place in January, according to the report. Oslo-based Point
Carbon, a provider of research on environmental markets, is a
unit of Thomson Reuters Corp.  “We don’t comment on market investigations as a matter of
policy, however, any market-related matters for members or
customers would be communicated directly,” Brookly McLaughlin,
a spokeswoman for Intercontinental Exchange Inc. in  Chicago ,
said today by e-mail.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  